    "body": "## Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Have Beta 101.0.0-beta.1 installed.\r\n2. Open a page.\r\n3. From the three-dot menu go to Settings - General - Theme.\r\n4. Select \"Light\" or \"Dark\".\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nThe selected theme has the checked radio button. The user remains in the General page.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nThe selected theme is applied. The user is redirected to a new tab opened.\r\nThe new opened tab is similar to the tab opened in step 2.\r\nIf there is no tab opened, a new tab is opened with the previos tab opened.\r\n\r\n### Device information\r\n* Android device: Oppo Reno 6 (Android 12)\r\n* Focus version: Beta 101.0.0-beta.1\r\n* Not reproducible on Focus nightly 102.0a1 from 5/3, nor on RC 100.1.1\r\n* After clearing the data, I was not able to reproduce the issue again.\r\n* logcat: [logcat.txt](https://github.com/mozilla-mobile/focus-android/files/8611118/logcat.txt)\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40694158/166473219-df5a297c-4db6-4631-bf7d-a212bcbdc0a6.mp4\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40694158/166473237-fb498c5a-66f1-4f03-9dc8-1e730faef331.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n",
